# Exact Rewrite Architecture Screening

Reusable findings from the Step-5 screen that fixed one inherited estimate
architecture and one bad term for the beyond-De Giorgi exact-rewrite audit.

## Entries

- `local-energy-flux-localization-is-the-right-inherited-architecture-for-the-exact-rewrite-audit.md`:
  the local-energy localization framework is the fairest inherited home for
  comparing bounded exact rewrites because it exposes the localized cutoff
  cost directly.
- `de-giorgi-truncation-is-too-entangled-with-closed-pressure-negatives-for-this-audit.md`:
  the De Giorgi option is not a clean Step-5 choice because the local record
  already closes its main pressure-facing targets.
- `stretching-localization-mismatches-the-rewrite-audit-and-reopens-a-killed-branch.md`:
  the stretching-localization option would test the wrong mechanism and
  effectively reopen the geometry branch already screened out.
- `the-localized-lei-cutoff-flux-bundle-is-the-fixed-bad-term-for-the-audit.md`:
  the localized LEI cutoff-flux bundle is the exact term that later rewrite
  comparisons must keep fixed.
- `success-requires-a-smaller-effective-lei-cutoff-flux-cost-in-the-same-protocol.md`:
  later success only counts if a rewrite yields the chosen gain currency,
  namely a smaller effective LEI cutoff-flux cost under the same protocol
  after all inherited projection and commutator burdens are paid.
- `step-013-burden-ledger-uses-eight-currencies-around-the-fixed-lei-cutoff-flux-bundle.md`:
  Step-013 records the typed burden ledger that later candidates must use to
  post derivative, locality, cancellation, integrability, pressure,
  admissibility, compactness, and scaling claims against the same live LEI
  bundle.
- `same-currency-comparisons-only-count-on-the-same-full-lei-object-protocol-and-charged-debt.md`:
  direct comparison is only honest on the same full `I_flux[phi]` object,
  solution class, cutoff protocol, and charged debt.
- `cross-currency-claims-need-an-explicit-transfer-lemma-back-to-the-full-lei-bundle.md`:
  derivative, integrability, surrogate-cancellation, or compactness-side
  gains only count if an explicit transfer lemma brings them back to a
  smaller coefficient on the full LEI bundle.

