+# Step-014 Active Exact-Rewrite Slate Fails First At Endpoint Exchange
+
+Status: `INFERRED` Step-014 verdict with `VERIFIED` active-slate and comparator support
+
+The Step-014 endpoint-exchange audit resolves the active exact-rewrite slate
+before any later anti-repackaging continuation is earned.
+
+Once the theorem-facing burden is frozen to the full localized LEI cutoff-flux
+bundle `I_flux[phi]`, both active Step-2 candidates fail first on the same
+question: neither packet gives a same-currency cash-out or an explicit
+transfer lemma back to a positive-margin smaller full-bundle coefficient after
+visible debt is restored.
+
+- For `Lamb-vector / Helmholtz-projected form`, the missing exchange is a
+  theorem-level estimate turning projected Lamb-vector or localized
+  Beltrami-deficit control into a smaller `I_flux[phi]` coefficient after
+  pressure, projection, and cutoff debt.
+- For `vorticity transport / Biot-Savart form`, the missing exchange is a
+  localized estimate turning `omega`-side substitution plus reconstruction
+  back into a smaller `I_flux[phi]` coefficient after Biot-Savart, pressure,
+  and cutoff debt.
+
+That is enough to stop the slate on the frozen ledger. The nearest-prior-art
+audit strengthens the negative result by showing that both packets are
+recycled versions of already-audited local comparators, but prior-art overlap
+is supporting context rather than the primary kill label here.
+
+Because `divergence / stress form` was already reserve-only and weaker still,
+the honest Step-014 branch verdict is `exchange-failure obstruction`: the
+active slate should stop before Step 3 and before anti-repackaging is treated
+as the first live gate.
+
